txml

Interface Node

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TNode

    public interface Node
    The Node interface is the primary datatype for the entire TXML model. It represents a single node in the document tree. While all objects implementing the Node interface expose methods for dealing with children, not all objects implementing the Node interface may have children. For example, Text nodes may not have children, and adding children to such nodes results in a TXmlException being raised.

    The attributes nodeName, nodeValue and attributes are included as a mechanism to get at node information without casting down to the specific derived interface. In cases where there is no obvious mapping of these attributes for a specific nodeType (e.g. nodeValue for an Element), this returns empty result.

    Author:
    Tomas Kunovsky
